Package us.hebi.quickbuf

Class JsonSource

java.lang.Object
us.hebi.quickbuf.JsonSource
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, AutoCloseable
public abstract class JsonSource extends Object implements Closeable
Reads proto messages from a JSON format compatible with

https://developers.google.com/protocol-buffers/docs/proto3#json

Since:
08 Sep 2020

    • setIgnoreUnknownFields

      public JsonSource setIgnoreUnknownFields(boolean ignoreUnknownFields)
      Allows to serialize enums as human readable strings or as JSON numbers. Compatible parsers are able to parse either case.

      Unknown values will still be serialized as numbers.

      Parameters:
      ignoreUnknownFields - true if values should use strings
      Returns:
      this

    • readDouble

      public abstract double readDouble() throws IOException
      Read a double field value from the source.

      JSON value will be a number or one of the special string values "NaN", "Infinity", and "-Infinity". Either numbers or strings are accepted. Exponent notation is also accepted. -0 is considered equivalent to 0.

      Throws:
      IOException

      public abstract <T extends ProtoEnum<?>> T readEnum(ProtoEnum.EnumConverter<T> converter) throws IOException
      Read a enum field value from the source.

      The name of the enum value as specified in proto is used. Parsers accept both enum names and integer values.

      Returns:
